          <p class='first-para'>
            In view of the amendment I have moved, Amendment No. 62, it may be that the noble Earl in a position to move Amendment No. 64 when he could not move Amendment No. 63. Nevertheless, as I understand it, what he is seeking to do with Amendment No. 64 is effectively embraced within what I have introduced by way of Amendment No. 62. On that basis, I hope he will withdraw it.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0564P0-04887'>
        <a name='S5LV0564P0_19950606_GCR_400'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-james-erskine-1' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0564P0_19950606_GCR_400' title='Link to this speech by Mr James Erskine' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-james-erskine-1" title="Mr James Erskine">The Earl of Mar and Kellie</a></cite>
